SUMMARY:IMPROMPTU: Gap Still Nifty 45
DESCRIPTION:Lancaster Bicycle Club (LBC) Meetup\nRide Leader: Lynn Pfeil\n
 \nThis is a training ride for a few of us participating in America's Most 
 Beautiful Bike Ride for Blood Cancer United\, in Lake Tahoe on June 7th bu
 t **ALL ARE WELCOME**! Our pace will probably be about 14 but you can ride
  FASTER! I created this route\, loosely based on my Hans Herr Nifty Fifty.
  It is largely flat but includes Mentzer and Cat's Back. There are many po
 tential rest stops along the way.\n(noted on RWGPS)\nLink to the ride: [ht
 tps://ridewithgps.com/routes/54526163](https://ridewithgps.com/routes/5452
 6163)\n\nInterested in **donating to Blood Cancer United** (formerly the L
 eukemia and Lymphoma Society)? http://tinyurl.com/tahoe26\n\nInterested in
  **joining us in Lake Tahoe**? [https://pages.lls.org/events/home/ambbr202
 6#register-section](https://pages.lls.org/events/home/ambbr2026#register-s
 ection)\n\nHelmets are mandatory. No ear buds. Please bring water and a ba
 sic repair kit (spare tube\, tire levers\, pump/CO2 inflator).\nTo elimina
 te passing around a pen and paper waiver\, we require LBC Club membership 
 and Meetup RSVP below to join this ride.\nBeing on Meetup does not mean yo
 u are a club member. [Join here](https://www.lancasterbikeclub.net/content
 .aspx?page_id=60&club_id=257148).\nYour RSVP is your agreement to abide by
  the club's [Code of Conduct](https://lancbikeclub.clubexpress.com/content
 .aspx?page_id=22&club_id=257148&module_id=323984) \,\n[Rules of the Road](
 https://lancbikeclub.clubexpress.com/content.aspx?page_id=22&club_id=25714
 8&module_id=325159) \, and [Ride Waiver](https://lancasterbikeclub.net/doc
 s.ashx?id=454318)
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/lancaster-bicycle-club/events/3141373
 03/
